Menu="Utilities"
Title="ShipLog"
Icon="anchor"
---
<?php
/* ShipLog settings → writes /boot/config/plugins/shiplog/shiplog.cfg via Unraid's
   /update.php, then restarts the daemon. NB: do not define functions in a .page
   (Unraid may include it more than once → "Cannot redeclare" → blank page); read
   the values inline instead. */
$cfg    = parse_plugin_cfg("shiplog");
$enable = isset($cfg['ENABLE']) ? $cfg['ENABLE'] : 'true';
$port   = !empty($cfg['PORT'])          ? $cfg['PORT']          : '8484';
$ddir   = !empty($cfg['DATA_DIR'])      ? $cfg['DATA_DIR']      : '/mnt/user/appdata/shiplog';
$poll   = !empty($cfg['POLL_INTERVAL']) ? $cfg['POLL_INTERVAL'] : '6h';
$ghtok  = isset($cfg['GITHUB_TOKEN'])      ? $cfg['GITHUB_TOKEN']      : '';
$ourl   = isset($cfg['OLLAMA_URL'])        ? $cfg['OLLAMA_URL']        : '';
$omodel = isset($cfg['OLLAMA_MODEL'])      ? $cfg['OLLAMA_MODEL']      : '';
$mhs    = isset($cfg['MATRIX_HOMESERVER']) ? $cfg['MATRIX_HOMESERVER'] : '';
$mtok   = isset($cfg['MATRIX_TOKEN'])      ? $cfg['MATRIX_TOKEN']      : '';
$mroom  = isset($cfg['MATRIX_ROOM'])       ? $cfg['MATRIX_ROOM']       : '';
?>

<form markdown="1" name="shiplog_settings" method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
<input type="hidden" name="#file" value="shiplog/shiplog.cfg">
<input type="hidden" name="#command" value="/usr/local/emhttp/plugins/shiplog/scripts/rc.shiplog">
<input type="hidden" name="#arg[1]" value="restart">

ShipLog is **read-only** — it never updates, pulls or stops anything; it only shows what changed between your running image and the newest one, as a small control in the Docker tab's update column.

_(Enable engine)_:
: <select name="ENABLE">
  <option value="true"  <?=$enable!=='false'?'selected':''?>>Yes</option>
  <option value="false" <?=$enable==='false'?'selected':''?>>No</option>
  </select>

_(Engine port)_:
: <input type="text" class="narrow" name="PORT" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($port)?>"> &nbsp; <span id="sl-statuslink"></span>

_(Data directory)_:
: <input type="text" name="DATA_DIR" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($ddir)?>"> (SQLite cache — keep on appdata, not the flash)

_(Poll interval)_:
: <input type="text" class="narrow" name="POLL_INTERVAL" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($poll)?>"> (Go duration: 1h, 6h, 24h)

_(GitHub token)_:
: <input type="password" name="GITHUB_TOKEN" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($ghtok)?>"> (a classic PAT, no scopes needed — raises the changelog API rate limit)

_(Ollama URL — optional)_:
: <input type="text" name="OLLAMA_URL" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($ourl)?>"> (e.g. http://127.0.0.1:11434)

_(Ollama model — optional)_:
: <input type="text" name="OLLAMA_MODEL" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($omodel)?>">

_(Matrix homeserver — optional)_:
: <input type="text" name="MATRIX_HOMESERVER" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($mhs)?>">

_(Matrix token — optional)_:
: <input type="password" name="MATRIX_TOKEN" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($mtok)?>">

_(Matrix room — optional)_:
: <input type="text" name="MATRIX_ROOM" value="<?=htmlspecialchars($mroom)?>">

&nbsp;
: <input type="submit" name="#apply" value="Apply"><input type="button" value="Done" onclick="done()">

</form>

<script>
(function () {
  var port = "<?=htmlspecialchars($port)?>";
  var a = document.getElementById("sl-statuslink");
  if (a) a.innerHTML = 'Status page: <a href="http://' + location.hostname + ':' + port + '/" target="_blank">http://' + location.hostname + ':' + port + '/</a>';
})();
</script>
